				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/grigori-karpin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4558017); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=4558017&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610226984" alt="Grigori Karpin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=4558017)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/grigori-karpin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(4558017); return false;" >Grigori Karpin</a></span> <span class="odate time_1602125365 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">08 Oct 2020 02:49</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4791200">
									

<p>So I liked this plenty but I’ve got some confusion:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">►&nbsp;Some&nbsp;detailed&nbsp;thoughts◄</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">▼&nbsp;close&nbsp;▼</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>The unfounded canon is roughly such that the SCP Foundation doesn’t exist but the veil is still up according to the canon page&#8230; this story feels more like we’re in a world where the anomalies are ever present, and I don’t get that&#8230; maybe it’s something that will be revealed later, but it struck me as odd.</p>
<p>Also confused why the first link goes back to this same page?</p>
<blockquote>
<p><em>ever to have been invited to join them right out of the academy.&quot;</em></p>
</blockquote>
<p>Broken italics here</p>
<p>In fact there’s a lot of sections out of italics and I’m not sure what the italics represent, the flashback goes in and out of it, but some of the prose is in italics and some isn’t</p>
<p>I will say there’s quite a few errors here with punctuation, like “ inside the period and another time there’s incorrect “ around something in a quote, which should be ‘</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>This leaves a lot to be explained but I assume that will flow from the next parts. It was interesting enough to +1 but I’m pretty unsatisfied with the arc, as it seems only to be an opening chapter. More could be done to make sure that each tale stands on its own as best you can.</p>

							</div>

								
					
