<p>Hi! The italics are primarily used for internalized, conscious thoughts. Some of the prose is actually Adrian's thoughts, which is why some is italicized. The rest is purely the author.</p>
<p>As for this:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The unfounded canon is roughly such that the SCP Foundation doesn’t exist but the veil is still up according to the canon page… this story feels more like we’re in a world where the anomalies are ever present, and I don’t get that…</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is because the setting is within the Free Port Eurtec, which is considered to be openly anomalous, which is why it appears more *frequently* for a lack of a better term.</p>
<p>As for the issues regarding it standing on its own, that may be an issue with how the contest explicitly wants each article entered to flow with each other, and connect directly. But yes, we will try to work on making things stay structurely more sound.</p>
<p>I will also be fixing the grammatical mistakes momentarily, thank you!</p>
</div>
