<p>I like this on the whole, but the decision to put an offset in the middle of the page is a pretty weird choice. It's very weird to open the offset, read the information there, and then return to the middle of the page. I'd recommend splitting the first offset into two pages, one before and one after the second offset.</p>
<p>Also, the first line of the tale would be much better served by swapping the order of the clauses. As it currently stands, it isn't clear what the traits describe: Halfway Central Station or the other twelve. In fact, it's more likely to be the other twelve. If you put the adjectives first, it would be a lot clearer.</p>

